properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 3:57AM PST until January 12 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snowfall of 2 to 5 inches are expected above 3500 feet.
Locally higher amounts possible in the Trinity Alps.

* WHERE...Northern Trinity County.

* WHEN...From 7 AM to 10 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Chains or snow tires may be needed over Scott Mountain
Summit due to hazardous driving conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state of California can be
obtained by calling 1-800-GAS-ROAD.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 10 PM PST SUNDAY ABOVE 3500 FEET
